        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20cases.20on.20fin.201/near/284695906\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>By the way, do you know about the <code>linear_combination</code> tactic?  It will give the values of <code>g 0</code> and <code>g 1</code> much more easily.</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"n\">h1</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">g</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">linear_combination</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h.1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h.2</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">),</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I tried this, and got an error.</p>",
